The Initial Problem: While LS was a widely used "trick" to improve model accuracy in tasks like image classification and translation, it was poorly understood
. There was little empirical evidence explaining how it modified internal representations or why it improved performance
.
Dangers of Overconfidence: Modern neural networks tend to be poorly calibrated and overconfident, meaning their predicted probabilities are higher than their actual accuracy
. This overconfidence is harmful to downstream tasks like beam-search in machine translation, which relies on calibrated likelihoods to function correctly
.
Mechanism of Label Smoothing:
Target Modification: LS replaces "hard" 0/1 targets with soft targets—a weighted average of the hard label and a uniform distribution across all labels
.
Representation Clustering: It forces penultimate layer activations into tight, equally distant clusters
. Each example is encouraged to be close to its class "template" and equidistant to all incorrect class templates
.
Advantages:
Improved Generalization: It consistently boosts accuracy and learning speed
.
Implicit Calibration: It "automatically" calibrates models, making confidence scores a more reliable measure of accuracy without needing post-processing like temperature scaling
.
Enhanced Translation: By improving calibration, it leads to better BLEU scores in translation models
.
Limitations:
Knowledge Distillation Failure: If a teacher model is trained with LS, it becomes an inferior teacher
. Distillation into a student is much less effective because the teacher’s "clean" logits lose the nuanced information about class similarities
.
Information Erasure: LS erases the relative information (or "dark knowledge") about resemblances between different classes
.
Future Extensions:
Information Bottleneck: Further research into how LS relates to compression and generalization through information bottleneck theory
.
Non-Uniform Smoothing: Exploring unigram label smoothing for datasets where class distributions are highly imbalanced
.
Transfer Learning: Investigating the impact of LS on information transfer to new tasks
.